Stat!

18:36.908 --> 18:37.949
What happened?

18:38.075 --> 18:40.076
Pills. Benzos. We need to get
her stomach pumped.

18:40.203 --> 18:41.953
- Respiration's shallow.
- What did you say to her?

18:42.079 --> 18:43.163
Nothing that would
make her want to...

18:43.289 --> 18:44.122
Heartbeat's irregular.

18:44.248 --> 18:45.457
- What did she say to you?
- Nothing.

18:45.583 --> 18:47.167
I gave her a couple of sedatives,
turned around,

18:47.293 --> 18:49.294
- and she grabbed the whole bottle.
- You must have said something.

18:49.420 --> 18:51.588
I said plenty.
She said nothing.

18:51.714 --> 18:53.089
I was with her
for over an hour.

18:53.216 --> 18:55.050
She didn't say one word.

19:23.704 --> 19:25.247
You gonna do that again?

19:30.253 --> 19:32.546
You're gonna be okay.
Physically.

19:34.340 --> 19:36.758
Which is all
that interests you.

19:41.013 --> 19:42.514
But you're here.

19:43.057 --> 19:44.140
Under orders.

19:45.601 --> 19:47.561
Why would you tell me that?

19:47.687 --> 19:49.729
'Cause I don't
like hypocrisy.

19:50.064 --> 19:52.399
But you don't have
a problem with cruelty?

19:55.403 --> 19:58.905
Which brings us back to,
why do you want me?

19:59.991 --> 20:00.949
I don't know.

20:02.451 --> 20:05.161
You tried to kill yourself
because you couldn't talk to me.

20:05.288 --> 20:06.121
You must have a reason.

20:06.247 --> 20:08.039
Why does there always
have to be a reason?

20:08.165 --> 20:09.916
Can't we just talk?

20:10.209 --> 20:12.002
There's a phone.
Talk to a friend,

20:12.295 --> 20:14.296
a family member.
Call the police.

20:20.636 --> 20:23.221
You want to talk about
what happened to you?

20:23.347 --> 20:24.472
No.

20:26.434 --> 20:28.560
You want to talk
about your STD meds?

20:28.686 --> 20:30.186
No.

20:31.105 --> 20:33.356
You don't really
seem to want to talk.

20:33.482 --> 20:34.649
No, I do.

20:35.484 --> 20:36.610
About what?

20:38.195 --> 20:40.655
I don't know. Anything.

20:42.158 --> 20:43.617
The weather?

20:45.995 --> 20:49.080
You were raped and
you want to talk about the weather?

20:50.583 --> 20:51.708
Yeah.

20:53.961 --> 20:56.713
I'm not gonna talk to
you about the weather.

21:03.095 --> 21:05.055
- You help her.
- She wants you.

21:05.181 --> 21:06.014
God knows why.

21:06.766 --> 21:07.807
She doesn't know
what she wants.

21:07.934 --> 21:10.727
She knows she wants you. You were the
first person she spoke to about this.

21:10.853 --> 21:12.896
The fact that I
was in the wrong place at the wrong time

21:13.022 --> 21:14.898
should be trumped by the fact
that I'm useless at this.

21:15.149 --> 21:16.566
No, you're not.

21:17.234 --> 21:19.235
You romantically
wanting to believe that

21:19.362 --> 21:21.237
is never going
to make it true.

21:22.573 --> 21:24.115
I'm agreeing with you.

21:24.241 --> 21:27.369
You're the last person
she should be talking to.

21:27.787 --> 21:30.288
If she wants to talk about the weather,
talk about the weather.

21:30.414 --> 21:33.208
She wants normalcy. She wants to feel
like the world didn't end.

21:33.334 --> 21:36.336
Right. I'll tell her
that everything went on without her.

21:36.587 --> 21:38.838
Babies were born,
people got married,

21:38.965 --> 21:41.132
thousands of people
will remember the day she got raped

21:41.258 --> 21:42.300
as the happiest
day of their lives.

21:42.426 --> 21:44.552
You might not want to
phrase it quite that way.

21:44.679 --> 21:46.388
You need to get her to
talk about what happened.

21:46.514 --> 21:47.347
No, he doesn't.

21:47.473 --> 21:48.306
Pretending it didn't happen...

21:48.432 --> 21:49.724
Wrong.
Pretending this didn't happen

21:49.850 --> 21:51.184
is the best thing
she could possibly do.

21:51.310 --> 21:52.519
She's got to make this real.

21:52.645 --> 21:55.188
You know what we should
be trying to make real or process?

21:55.314 --> 21:57.857
The few decent
moments in our lives. Not the crap.

21:57.984 --> 21:59.526
Maybe you're right.
Except there's no way

21:59.652 --> 22:01.403
she can pretend
this didn't happen.

22:01.529 --> 22:04.114
So she has no choice
but to process it.

22:06.701 --> 22:09.119
You've got to tell me
what happened.

22:09.453 --> 22:11.621
You don't
really want to hear.

22:11.747 --> 22:13.039
Sure I do.

22:13.666 --> 22:15.000
You're lying.

22:17.461 --> 22:20.005
This doesn't have
to destroy your life.

22:20.464 --> 22:21.631
I know.

22:21.757 --> 22:23.466
It doesn't mean
anything about you.

22:23.592 --> 22:25.468
It wasn't your fault.

22:25.636 --> 22:26.845
I know.

22:26.971 --> 22:28.471
You did nothing wrong.

22:28.597 --> 22:30.306
Some jerk hurt you.
That's all.

22:30.433 --> 22:31.558
I know.

22:31.809 --> 22:34.394
You're worried that you can
never trust men again.

22:34.520 --> 22:35.353
No.

22:35.479 --> 22:37.439
Statistically, there was always a chance
this could happen.

22:37.565 --> 22:40.066
The fact that it did happen
doesn't change anything.

22:40.192 --> 22:42.902
The world doesn't suck any more today
than it did yesterday.

22:43.029 --> 22:43.862
I know all that.

22:44.238 --> 22:45.655
Well, then what do
you want me to tell you?

22:45.781 --> 22:49.075
Nothing. I just want to talk.

22:49.452 --> 22:53.329
About nothing. If we talk about nothing,
nothing will change.

22:54.123 --> 22:55.415
It might.

22:55.541 --> 22:56.833
How?

22:56.959 --> 22:58.251
Time.

23:00.921 --> 23:02.589
Time changes everything.

23:03.799 --> 23:05.925
That's what people say.
It's not true.

23:06.135 --> 23:08.261
Doing things changes things.

23:08.679 --> 23:12.807
Not doing things leaves things
exactly as they were.

23:19.148 --> 23:21.191
Why do you have to suffer?

23:22.610 --> 23:24.027
I gave my word.

23:25.029 --> 23:26.613
Who would make
you promise that?

23:26.739 --> 23:28.198
My father.

23:29.909 --> 23:32.869
He said I would die
alone and miserable.

23:33.120 --> 23:34.079
That's not a promise.

23:34.205 --> 23:35.955
And even if it was,
he's dead.

23:36.082 --> 23:38.208
And even if he's not,
he's not going to care if...

23:38.334 --> 23:40.835
Why did your husband
have to suffer?

23:41.087 --> 23:45.006
- How do you know about my husband?
- Well, I just know.

23:50.471 --> 23:52.013
You have to die in pain

23:52.139 --> 23:54.766
because of a promise
you made to your father?

23:54.892 --> 24:00.063
If I say "yes," you'll use that
as proof that I'm insane.

24:01.482 --> 24:03.316
Force treatment on me.

24:04.610 --> 24:06.611
Did the nurse tell you
about my husband?

24:06.821 --> 24:08.238
No.

24:12.034 --> 24:13.535
- Nurse!
- Yes.

24:15.663 --> 24:17.288
It's under control.

24:22.503 --> 24:26.714
I'm sorry. I was just
trying to freak you out.

24:27.007 --> 24:28.133
Why?

24:28.259 --> 24:30.385
Because I need you
to remember me.

24:30.553 --> 24:33.012
I need somebody
to remember me.

24:38.352 --> 24:40.103
Where did you go to college?

24:40.229 --> 24:42.313
Northwestern. You?

24:42.982 --> 24:45.608
Hopkins. What was your major?

24:46.068 --> 24:47.277
Comparative religion.

24:47.403 --> 24:48.486
Why do you trust me?

24:48.612 --> 24:50.113
I don't know.
Can't we just...

24:50.239 --> 24:51.239
That's not rational.

24:51.365 --> 24:52.448
Nothing's rational.

24:52.575 --> 24:53.616
Everything is rational!

24:53.742 --> 24:55.326
I was raped.

24:55.452 --> 24:57.620
Explain how that
makes sense to you.

25:00.666 --> 25:05.086
We are selfish, base animals
crawling across the earth,

25:05.212 --> 25:08.173
and because we've got brains,
if we try real hard,

25:08.299 --> 25:12.093
we can occasionally aspire to something
that is less than pure evil.

25:18.392 --> 25:21.269
Has anything terrible
ever happened to you?

25:24.565 --> 25:26.524
What do you want me to say?

25:27.776 --> 25:29.652
You wanted this conversation.

25:30.237 --> 25:34.157
You wanted to talk about
something that matters. Talk.

25:40.497 --> 25:42.290
She's waiting
for your answer?

25:42.416 --> 25:43.833
She's asleep.

25:45.336 --> 25:46.711
I sedated her.

25:48.589 --> 25:50.006
Why do you care
what you say to her?

25:50.132 --> 25:53.009
Because I don't know how to
answer these questions.

25:53.135 --> 25:55.720
It's a simple question.
"Has your life sucked?"

25:55.846 --> 25:58.306
Tell her the truth.
Tell her you were shot. Tell her...

25:58.432 --> 25:59.891
She doesn't want
to hear the truth.

26:00.017 --> 26:01.351
She's looking for something.

26:01.477 --> 26:02.602
Looking to
extrapolate some...

26:02.728 --> 26:04.103
She's looking to
connect with you.

26:04.438 --> 26:07.607
And that's what's scaring the hell
out of you. Tell her the truth.

26:07.733 --> 26:09.067
There is no truth.

26:11.237 --> 26:12.862
Are we role-playing?

26:12.988 --> 26:14.239
Am I you?
I don't want to be you.

26:14.365 --> 26:16.199
She's not asking
for test results.

26:16.325 --> 26:18.368
She's not asking what
two plus two equals.

26:18.494 --> 26:20.328
She's asking for my
personal life experience

26:20.454 --> 26:22.455
so she can extrapolate
to all humanity.

26:22.581 --> 26:25.166
That's not truth.
It's bad science.

26:26.252 --> 26:30.463
It's not science at all.
Tell her the truth.

26:33.300 --> 26:34.842
Tell her your life
has been good.

26:34.969 --> 26:36.177
It hasn't been.

26:36.303 --> 26:38.221
Tell her anyway.
She wants hope.

26:38.347 --> 26:41.516
She wants to know that
what happened to her wasn't the norm.

26:41.642 --> 26:43.017
That things can be okay,

26:43.143 --> 26:45.728
which means maybe they can be
okay for her again.

26:48.607 --> 26:49.983
Tell her your life sucked.

26:50.109 --> 26:51.359
It didn't.

26:51.485 --> 26:52.694
Tell her anyway.

26:52.820 --> 26:54.237
She wants to know
she's not alone.

26:54.363 --> 26:56.030
She wants to know
she's gonna survive this.

26:56.156 --> 26:57.699
That other people
have been through this

26:57.825 --> 26:59.325
and worse and come
out the other end.

26:59.451 --> 27:01.536
She wants to know if
she's going to heal.

27:01.662 --> 27:03.997
Act like you've healed.

27:06.292 --> 27:07.792
Tell her...

27:10.921 --> 27:12.422
Keep her asleep.

27:13.674 --> 27:17.343
Thanks. You all
have been a huge help.

27:17.845 --> 27:20.054
There's no wrong answer.

27:20.222 --> 27:22.473
Because there's
no right answer.

27:22.599 --> 27:24.475
Wrong.

27:24.601 --> 27:26.686
We just don't know
what the right answer is.

27:32.943 --> 27:33.985
Wake up.

27:41.785 --> 27:44.495
It's not as bad as
what happened to you.

27:45.080 --> 27:46.414
I don't think.

27:46.540 --> 27:48.249
I don't know what
happened to you.

27:48.375 --> 27:49.751
But given how lousy
you're responding,

27:49.877 --> 27:53.504
I assume it was worse than
getting abused by your grandmother.

27:56.967 --> 27:58.760
What did she do to you?

28:00.679 --> 28:02.263
Parents traveled a lot.

28:02.389 --> 28:04.265
They'd leave me with her.

28:05.100 --> 28:07.477
She liked things
the way she liked them.

28:07.603 --> 28:09.645
And she believed
in discipline.

28:09.897 --> 28:11.022
She was right, I suppose,

28:11.148 --> 28:14.150
because I hardly ever
screwed up when she was around.

28:14.276 --> 28:18.279
Too scared of getting forced
to sleep in the yard

28:18.405 --> 28:19.739
or take a bath in ice.

28:24.870 --> 28:25.995
Your turn.

28:28.582 --> 28:31.376
Your parents,
they never stopped her?

28:32.503 --> 28:34.003
I never told them.

28:34.421 --> 28:35.713
Why not?

28:36.423 --> 28:37.507
Usual reasons.

28:37.633 --> 28:39.258
I was afraid they
wouldn't believe me.

28:39.385 --> 28:42.345
I was afraid they'd think
I'd done something wrong.

28:46.183 --> 28:48.768
I opened up to you.
You open up to me.

28:49.520 --> 28:50.770
What did you call her?

28:50.896 --> 28:51.938
Oma.

28:52.064 --> 28:53.856
And you kept calling
her that after this?

28:54.024 --> 28:57.068
Dutch for "grandmother."
She was still my grandmother.

28:57.194 --> 28:59.028
And she was still Dutch.

29:04.243 --> 29:06.661
Is any part of
that story true?

29:07.788 --> 29:09.122
All of it.

29:09.248 --> 29:11.249
You wouldn't keep
calling her Oma.

29:11.375 --> 29:13.334
Something would
have to change.

29:13.460 --> 29:14.293
You don't know me.

29:14.461 --> 29:16.712
You wouldn't keep
calling her Oma!

29:16.839 --> 29:19.590
- Look, you're over-reacting...
- Do not dismiss me.

29:19.716 --> 29:20.550
I'm not dismissing you.

29:20.676 --> 29:22.385
I'm saying you're
not acting rationally.

29:22.636 --> 29:24.303
I'm angry because
you are lying to me!

29:24.471 --> 29:26.139
- No, you are...
- What can I do?

29:26.265 --> 29:28.141
What the hell can I do
that you're not gonna dismiss

29:28.350 --> 29:30.810
as just being
because I was raped?

29:34.731 --> 29:36.023
Nothing.

29:39.570 --> 29:43.030
Your story, is it true?

29:45.159 --> 29:46.951
True for somebody.

29:48.078 --> 29:49.537
But not for you.

29:50.038 --> 29:51.205
These things happen.

29:51.832 --> 29:53.124
It happened to somebody.

29:53.250 --> 29:54.876
What do you care
if it happened to me?

29:55.002 --> 29:57.712
- They're not in this room.
- No, they're out there!

29:57.838 --> 30:00.047
Doctors, lawyers,
postal workers.

30:00.215 --> 30:02.258
Some of them doing great,
some of them doing lousy.

30:02.593 --> 30:04.051
You gonna base
your whole life

30:04.261 --> 30:05.761
on who you got
stuck in a room with?

30:05.888 --> 30:09.390
I'm gonna base this moment
on who I'm stuck in a room with.

30:10.309 --> 30:13.478
It's what life is.
It's a series of rooms.

30:14.229 --> 30:16.814
And who we get stuck
in those rooms with

30:16.940 --> 30:19.025
adds up to what
our lives are.

30:26.033 --> 30:27.617
House?

30:42.049 --> 30:43.674
You gotta get me out of this.

30:43.800 --> 30:45.384
There's nothing to diagnose.
There's nothing...

30:45.511 --> 30:47.470
You only tested her for STDs?

30:47.888 --> 30:50.306
I had seven morons
who forgot their raincoats.

30:50.432 --> 30:52.975
It's all they asked for
so I didn't waste the lab's time. Why?

30:53.101 --> 30:55.895
I wasted their time.
She's pregnant.

31:10.661 --> 31:12.203
Do you understand?

31:15.999 --> 31:17.583
Are you okay?

31:18.544 --> 31:20.628
I mean,
I know you're not okay.

31:21.129 --> 31:23.047
But are you more
or less not okay

31:23.173 --> 31:24.799
than you were
five minutes ago?

31:26.093 --> 31:27.552
About the same.

31:28.637 --> 31:30.179
Good.

31:30.305 --> 31:32.598
The termination
procedure isn't pleasant...

31:32.724 --> 31:34.600
I don't want to terminate.

31:36.144 --> 31:37.186
You want to keep the baby?

31:37.688 --> 31:39.272
Abortion is murder.

31:41.775 --> 31:46.237
True. It's a life.
And you should end it.

31:47.948 --> 31:49.490
Every life is sacred.

31:50.784 --> 31:53.911
Talk to me. Don't
quote me bumper stickers.

31:54.037 --> 31:55.454
- It's true.
- It's meaningless.

31:55.581 --> 31:57.248
It means every life
matters to God.

31:57.374 --> 31:59.208
Not to me, not to you.

31:59.501 --> 32:02.336
And judging by the number
of natural disasters, not to God either.

32:02.462 --> 32:03.588
You're just
being argumentative.

32:03.714 --> 32:05.131
Yeah. I do do that.

32:06.091 --> 32:07.383
What about Hitler?

32:07.509 --> 32:08.467
Was his life sacred to God?

32:09.219 --> 32:10.636
The father of your child?

32:10.762 --> 32:11.846
Is his life sacred to you?

32:11.972 --> 32:13.723
My child isn't Hitler.

32:13.849 --> 32:15.558
Either every life
is sacred or...

32:15.684 --> 32:18.686
Stop it! I don't want to
chat about philosophy!

32:18.979 --> 32:22.231
You're not killing your rape baby
because of a philosophy.

32:23.483 --> 32:26.485
It's murder.
I'm against it. You for it?

32:28.196 --> 32:29.405
Not as a general rule.

32:29.531 --> 32:30.740
Just for unborn children?

32:30.866 --> 32:31.991
Yes.

32:35.787 --> 32:39.665
The problem with exceptions
to rules is the line-drawing.

32:40.167 --> 32:43.044
It might make sense to kill the ass
that did this to you,

32:43.170 --> 32:44.837
but then where do
we draw the line?

32:44.963 --> 32:46.881
Which asses do
we get to kill?

32:47.007 --> 32:48.924
Which asses get to
keep on being asses?

32:49.259 --> 32:50.968
The nice thing about
the abortion debate

32:51.094 --> 32:52.803
is we can
quibble over trimesters

32:52.929 --> 32:57.767
but ultimately there's
a nice clean line, birth.

32:59.645 --> 33:01.520
Morally there's not
a lot of difference.

33:01.647 --> 33:03.356
Practically, huge.

33:04.858 --> 33:07.401
You're enjoying
this conversation.

33:09.237 --> 33:12.114
It's just the type of
conversation I do well.

33:14.451 --> 33:15.743
But the other type?

33:19.164 --> 33:20.790
The personal stuff?

33:23.418 --> 33:25.419
There are no answers.

33:25.671 --> 33:28.756
And if there are no answers,
why talk about it?

33:32.719 --> 33:36.430
You're healthy.
You shouldn't be here.

33:39.518 --> 33:41.227
I don't want to go.

33:44.189 --> 33:47.274
Fine. I won't discharge you.

33:53.657 --> 33:55.700
Wanna go for a walk?

34:02.666 --> 34:04.792
It's the last of my journey.

34:05.627 --> 34:07.628
You don't deserve pain.
You're just an insane old man.

34:07.754 --> 34:09.505
- No.
- I am not going to watch you suffer.

34:09.631 --> 34:11.048
I need you to remember me.

34:11.174 --> 34:13.426
- I'll remember you!
- Why?

34:13.593 --> 34:14.885
Because you're a nice man.

34:15.011 --> 34:17.972
You don't know that.
You don't know anything about me.

34:18.098 --> 34:19.724
Either you were a nice man
or you were an ass.

34:19.850 --> 34:23.436
Either way you did something to somebody
that they're going to remember.

34:23.562 --> 34:25.855
I have no family.
I have no friends.

34:26.022 --> 34:28.399
I didn't even
have a real job.

34:28.734 --> 34:30.568
If I die in peace,

34:30.694 --> 34:32.445
then I'm just
another patient.

34:32.571 --> 34:33.988
But if I die suffering...

34:34.114 --> 34:37.491
It'll be horrible. Don't
do that to either of us.

34:37.617 --> 34:42.538
No. I just need to
die knowing that something is different

34:42.706 --> 34:44.623
because I was here.

35:25.540 --> 35:27.208
Life goes on.

35:28.668 --> 35:31.462
Is that the reason
why we're out here?

35:31.880 --> 35:33.714
Know why I come here?

35:33.840 --> 35:36.675
I sit. I watch. I imagine.

35:39.805 --> 35:41.305
Sounds nice.

35:41.681 --> 35:44.433
I imagine that one of
them will break a leg.

35:44.643 --> 35:48.604
Just one false step,
one crack in the sidewalk...

35:49.898 --> 35:51.148
You don't really.

35:51.274 --> 35:52.483
I'm evil.

35:52.734 --> 35:55.152
Evil people don't
say they're evil.

35:55.278 --> 35:57.655
That sounds like
an easy loophole.

36:00.659 --> 36:04.453
People can do good things,
but their instincts are not good.

36:05.288 --> 36:08.624
Either God doesn't exist
or he's unimaginably cruel.

36:10.794 --> 36:12.545
I don't believe that.

36:13.463 --> 36:14.630
What do you believe?

36:15.090 --> 36:17.007
Why do you
think this happened?

36:19.553 --> 36:21.011
I don't want to
talk about it.

36:21.137 --> 36:23.806
Me neither. Too bad.

36:27.018 --> 36:29.770
You know, I don't think
there was a reason.

36:29.896 --> 36:32.565
So God does exist,
lets you get raped,

36:32.691 --> 36:35.609
needs you to keep
your rape baby for no reason.

36:38.488 --> 36:40.322
Maybe he was challenging me.

36:40.949 --> 36:42.616
He hurts you to help you.

36:44.452 --> 36:46.620
Well, I guess it's better
than because he hates you.

36:46.746 --> 36:48.747
You're trying to convince me
there's no God.

36:48.874 --> 36:50.249
Why would you even say
something like that?

36:50.375 --> 36:51.709
Because you're
throwing your life away.

36:51.835 --> 36:53.377
I'm doing what I believe!

36:53.503 --> 36:55.796
What you believe
doesn't make sense.

36:57.257 --> 36:58.757
This is not helping me.

36:58.925 --> 37:00.718
Then I can't help you.

37:03.179 --> 37:06.515
If you believe in eternity,
then life is irrelevant.

37:07.851 --> 37:09.351
The same way that
a bug is irrelevant

37:09.477 --> 37:11.312
in comparison
to the universe.

37:15.859 --> 37:17.860
If you don't
believe in eternity,

37:17.986 --> 37:19.862
then what you do here
is irrelevant.

37:19.988 --> 37:22.698
Your actions here
are all that matters.

37:22.824 --> 37:24.074
Then nothing matters.

37:24.200 --> 37:25.993
There's no
ultimate consequences.

37:28.204 --> 37:30.164
I couldn't live like that.

37:32.417 --> 37:34.376
So, you need to think
that the guy

37:34.502 --> 37:36.879
who did this to you is
going to be punished?

37:37.839 --> 37:40.549
I need to know that
it all means something.

37:41.801 --> 37:44.470
I need that comfort.

37:44.763 --> 37:47.723
Yeah.
Are you feeling comfortable?

37:49.392 --> 37:52.144
You feeling good right now?
You feel warm inside?

38:01.696 --> 38:06.784
I was raped.
What's your excuse?

39:04.175 --> 39:07.469
Do you think the guy who did
this to me feels bad?

39:08.513 --> 39:11.890
Would that help you?
Make you feel better?

39:13.143 --> 39:15.561
Why do you always do that?

39:15.729 --> 39:18.939
Ask why I'm asking questions
instead of just answering the question?

39:19.065 --> 39:21.066
The answer
doesn't interest me.

39:21.901 --> 39:23.402
I don't care
what he's feeling.

39:23.528 --> 39:26.030
I'm interested in
what you're feeling.

39:28.533 --> 39:29.867
You are?

39:33.955 --> 39:36.957
I'm trapped in
the room with you, right?

39:38.877 --> 39:40.753
Why did you choose me?

39:45.133 --> 39:47.384
There's something about you.

39:50.472 --> 39:52.389
It's like you're hurt, too.

40:05.779 --> 40:07.488
It was true.

40:10.492 --> 40:11.575
What was?

40:13.119 --> 40:15.913
It wasn't my grandmother.
But it was true.

40:20.210 --> 40:21.543
Who was it?

40:25.048 --> 40:26.673
It was my dad.

40:45.193 --> 40:48.028
I'd like to tell you
what happened to me now.

40:52.742 --> 40:54.701
I'd like to hear it.

41:02.794 --> 41:05.170
It was my friend's
birthday party...

41:55.763 --> 41:58.932
She terminated.
She's been discharged.

42:01.728 --> 42:03.687
She's going to be okay.

42:03.813 --> 42:05.898
Yeah. It's that simple.

42:08.151 --> 42:10.527
She's talking
about what happened.

42:10.695 --> 42:12.821
That's huge. You did good.

42:13.656 --> 42:17.367
And everyone'll tell you
that's what we gotta make her do.

42:17.493 --> 42:20.662
We got to help her, right?
Except we can't.

42:21.789 --> 42:26.835
We drag out her story,
tell each other that it'll help her heal

42:28.755 --> 42:31.089
and feel real good
about ourselves.

42:32.717 --> 42:35.802
Maybe all we've done
is make a girl cry.

42:37.305 --> 42:38.555
Then why did you...

42:43.019 --> 42:44.770
Because I don't know.

42:54.197 --> 42:56.365
You gonna follow up with her?

42:58.576 --> 43:01.453
One day, one room.
